{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bbcb2cff-3952-42b6-af1a-20e48cd21645","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_011TvZYvQvgUcCTWVW9ZV2ba","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4fad00d9e9d447cbba0a752c9b88d5bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4fad00d9e9d447cbba0a752c9b88d5bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"c107d9f5-e865-46e0-bc1d-6ad7ea1e8a18","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So it can't find it.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":411,"requestId":"7823:3738F9:FA0AA:135F7F:69F549F5"},"id":"d9a0bcfb-fe58-44a2-a72e-7372d566cabb","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:01.139Z","parentId":"58dcaf79-5e32-45b0-9387-259388a39da7"}
